# Skillet UI Layer

## XML + Lua Pairing

- Frame layout and widget names: `UI/*.xml` (e.g. `SkilletFrame`, `SkilletReagent1`)
- Behavior and updates: matching `UI/*.lua`
- New visible widgets: add to XML first, wire handlers in Lua. Register new UI files in `Skillet-Enhanced.toc` after `Utils.lua`

## Window Update Chain

Public entry points delegate to internals (defined in `ThirdPartyHooks.lua` / `MainFrame.lua`):

```
ShowTradeSkillWindow → internal_ShowTradeSkillWindow
UpdateTradeSkillWindow → internal_UpdateTradeSkillWindow
HideAllWindows → internal_HideAllWindows
```

UI refresh flows through tiered internals in `MainFrame.lua` (`internal_RefreshWindowChrome`, `internal_RefreshRecipeList`, `internal_RefreshInventoryCounts`, or full `internal_UpdateTradeSkillWindow`). Route cheap events to the narrowest tier; use full refresh only when structure or scan data changes.

## Lua 5.1 local function order

In Lua 5.1, a `local` name is **not** visible above its declaration line. A `local function` defined later in the file is **not** callable from earlier `local function` bodies — the name resolves as a nil global at runtime.

When adding module-local helpers in `UI/*.lua`:

1. Declare shared module locals first (`local num_recipe_buttons = 0`, caches, etc.)
2. Define helpers before callers, **or** use forward declaration: `local helper` then `helper = function ... end`
3. Prefer extending an existing helper with a parameter over duplicating a near-copy defined below the caller

See `tests/test_lua_scope.lua` for executable examples.

## Frame callback registration (dot vs colon)

Handlers passed to Blizzard frame APIs are invoked with **dot** syntax, so `self` inside a `function Skillet:Handler()` is **not** the addon:

| Registration | `self` at runtime |
|--------------|-------------------|
| `FauxScrollFrame_OnVerticalScroll(..., Skillet.Foo_OnScroll)` | Scroll frame |
| `info.func = Skillet.SortDropdown_OnClick` (UIDropDownMenu) | Menu button / args |
| XML `Skillet:Handler()` | Skillet (colon call) |
| `EnableResize(..., Skillet.UpdateTradeSkillWindow)` | Skillet (explicit first arg) |
| `AceEvent:ScheduleEvent(name, Skillet.Func, delay, Skillet)` | Skillet (packed first arg) |

For dot-registered handlers, define `function Skillet.HandlerName()` and use `Skillet:` / `Skillet.` for addon access — never `self:` for addon methods.

## WotLK frame Enable/Disable

On 3.3.5, `ScrollFrame` and plain `Frame` do **not** have `Enable()` / `Disable()`. Always guard with `if widget.Enable then` or use `set_widget_interaction` in `MainFrame.lua`. See [`skillet-wow-api.mdc`](skillet-wow-api.mdc).

## Existing UI Constants

Reuse module constants; do not magic-number duplicates:
- `SKILLET_TRADE_SKILL_HEIGHT`, `SKILLET_NUM_REAGENT_BUTTONS` (8 reagents max)
- `SKILLET_REAGENT_MIN_WIDTH` / `SKILLET_REAGENT_MAX_WIDTH`
- `skill_style_type` difficulty colors (optimal → trivial)

## Legacy Frame Access

Existing code uses `getglobal("SkilletReagent"..i)` — match this style in touched UI code; do not convert to `$parent` patterns in unrelated edits.

## Tooltips

- Recipe detail: `SkilletTradeskillTooltip` via `DisplayTradeskillTooltip`
- Hover tooltips: `SetTradeSkillToolTip(skill, reagentIndex)` — validate skill index and reagent slot before calling `GameTooltip:SetTradeSkillItem` (see `.docs/OVERVIEW.md` Known Issues)
- Prefer Stitch reagent links as fallback when Blizzard index is stale

## User-Facing Strings

All visible text through `L["KEY"]` — add keys to `Locale/Locale-enUS.lua` and mirror in other locale files (or set `true` for untranslated fallthrough).

## Combat Lockdown

Block frame open/toggle in combat the way existing commands do (`UnitAffectingCombat("player")` check with chat message).

## Resize & Appearance

- Sub-panel resize: `Skillet:EnableResize(frame, min_w, min_h, refresh_method)`
- Transparency/scale: `Skillet.db.profile.transparency` and `.scale` — apply via existing `UpdateTradeSkillWindow`, not direct one-off frame mutation
